It is understood that the behavior of euca-delete-bundle has changed.  Before, back during Euca 3.1.x days and before, a user could run euca-delete-bundle -b <bucket-name> --clear, and it would delete all the contents of the bucket.  The only requirement was that you had to deregister all the images that were registered in the bucket (my memory may be wrong here, but given that eustore bundles, uploads, and registers all images in one bucket, I think it was driven by that previous behavior for easier maintenance).  I also attempted to look back at AWS documentation when [--clear was first introduced|http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/2008-02-01/DeveloperGuide/index.html?CLTRG-ami-delete-bundle.html].  It doesn't give much insight as to the delete bundle behavior expected if you have multiple images thats are deregister in one bucket .
